text = "--Article 3: Potion-brewing is like baking, but with explosions!--

Brewing potions, unlike crafting artifacts, is not instantaneous and will consume time. You’ll still need to gather the necessary ingredients and follow the recipe, but you’ll have to leave them stewing in the cauldron for a while. You’re encouraged to multitask, but be careful of the time! A potion too little or too much concocted is a ruined potion, and a ruined potion doesn't make for very satisfied customers. 

--Article 4: It’s not a bright idea to monkey around with rituals--

Your final and most harrowing task will be rituals. Tricky, tricky things, rituals are. I’ve nearly lost all my internal organs more times than I can count in that blasted pentagram circle! You’ll need to focus only on the ritual when performing this job--no multitasking! 

